messages.message:
Yes, been playing with it. Pretty cool product similar to our own converse :slightly_smiling_face: Few initial observations.
• Supports collaborative editing! Candidly haven't tried this much.
• Supports upload from GDrive, website, and youtube! 
    ◦ I'm guessing Youtube is not multimodal but just the transcript.
• Only supports 50 docs relative to our 100. Doesn't have any digitization settings. 
    ◦ Does not support JPG/image formats. Does not support excel.
    ◦ Does decently on handwritten text for single doc. Haven't really pushed to try multidoc.
• Does fairly well with multidoc queries. 
• Provides citation level provenance - better than our page level provenance
• Allows saving "insights" generated by model as notes to refer back to. Particularly interesting for collaboration scenarios. 
cc: @Hari @Balaram @Clemens FYI
